<div class="instructions-wrapper">
  <div class="instructions-header">
    <h1 class="instructions-title">COVID-19 Spreadsheet Instructions</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="instructions-section">
    <div class="alert alert-warning">
      <strong>Please Note:</strong> COVID-19 spreadsheets are no longer actively generated. Please check the "Last Exported" date on the snapshots page for the most recent available data.
    </div>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      The following files contain clinical studies related to <span class="highlight">Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19)</span> from ClinicalTrials.gov as of the date and time of file creation.
      There may be more studies on ClinicalTrials.gov that were uploaded after the most recent file here.
      Each file allows users without advanced database skills to explore the trials in a spreadsheet format.
    </p>
    <p>
      The spreadsheet was created using <%= link_to "ClinicalTrials.gov's COVID-19 search criteria", "https://clinicaltrials.gov/search?cond=COVID-19", class: "inline-link", target: "_blank" %>
      and the database for Aggregate Analysis of ClinicalTrials.gov (AACT).
      This search strategy includes specific terms and filters to identify all <span class="highlight">COVID-19</span> related trials.
    </p>
    <p>
      Each study appears as a single row in the spreadsheet with 68 columns of study information. You can <a href='/covid_19_fields' class="inline-link">download</a> a detailed explanation of these fields, which include study identifiers, titles, conditions, interventions, locations, and results status.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="instructions-section">
    <h2>Using COVID-19 Data</h2>
    <div class="instruction-step">
      <div class="step-header">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <h3 class="step-title">Download a COVID-19 Spreadsheet</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <p>
          View and download available COVID-19 spreadsheets from our <%= link_to "COVID-19 spreadsheets", snapshots_downloads_path(type: "covid"), class: "inline-link" %> page.
          These files contain historical data from when COVID-19 spreadsheets were still being generated. For the most current clinical trial information, please visit <%= link_to "ClinicalTrials.gov", "https://clinicaltrials.gov/search?cond=COVID-19", class: "inline-link", target: "_blank" %> directly.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="instruction-step">
      <div class="step-header">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <h3 class="step-title">Working with the spreadsheet data</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <p>
          You can open the downloaded file in spreadsheet software like <span class="highlight">Microsoft Excel, Google Sheets, or LibreOffice Calc</span>.
          Each row represents a single clinical trial, with columns containing various attributes of the study.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>